# Instru√ß√µes para Hospedagem no GitHub Pages

## Passo a Passo para Hospedar o Site

### 1. Criar Reposit√≥rio no GitHub
1. Acesse [GitHub.com](https://github.com )
2. Clique em "New repository"
3. Nomeie o reposit√≥rio (ex: `campeoes-do-futuro-site`)
4. Marque como p√∫blico
5. Clique em "Create repository"

### 2. Fazer Upload dos Arquivos

#### Op√ß√£o A: Via Interface Web do GitHub
1. No reposit√≥rio criado, clique em "uploading an existing file"
2. Arraste todos os arquivos da pasta `/home/ubuntu/campeoes-site/`
3. Fa√ßa commit das mudan√ßas

#### Op√ß√£o B: Via Git (se voc√™ tem Git instalado)
```bash
git remote add origin https://github.com/SEU_USUARIO/NOME_DO_REPOSITORIO.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
name: Deploy to GitHub Pages

on:
  push:
    branches: [ main ]

jobs:
  build-and-deploy:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    
    steps:
    - name: Checkout
      uses: actions/checkout@v3
      
    - name: Setup Node.js
      uses: actions/setup-node@v3
      with:
        node-version: '18'
        
    - name: Install dependencies
      run: npm install
      
    - name: Build
      run: npm run build
      
    - name: Deploy
      uses: peaceiris/actions-gh-pages@v3
      with:
        github_token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
        publish_dir: ./dist


        
        
